parameters:
It seems like we can return from here.... Shall we return to
Codain?

To Donyoku-sama, the garden is nothing more than a showy
display... *sigh* I miss the time when I served at the Lira
House...
Could it be, Miss Vega...! Why are you here...? Could it be...?

So, you have some circumstances... If there's anything I can do
to help, please let me know. I may not be much, but I'll do my
best to be of service to you, Miss.
\SE[72]Thank you. \!\SE[7]I'll rely on you at that time.

Please be careful, Donyoku-sama. If anything were to happen to
the young lady, I... Ugh...
Oh, I forgot...!! I must give this to the young lady...

Actually, the young lady's father and I were old comrades- in-
arms... When we retired, we exchanged each other's dog tags as a
symbol of friendship.

\SE[90]...Huh? We were that close? \SE[3]I never showed any signs
of that at all.

It's because I was your father's superior officer. I suppose I
kept it hidden to maintain appearances.

After retiring, my subordinates quickly rose in rank and I ended
up working under them. It's actually quite embarrassing... Of
course, I don't feel that way myself.
\SE[90]I... I can't say I don't understand. \SE[4]But why me?

The 'dog tags' are just identification tags, but strangely, they
also gave the soldiers 'courage'. I thought that the young lady
is more deserving of having them than I am now.
\SE[72]I see... I understand. \.I will accept your kindness.

It seems that the mansion is being put up for sale. Therefore, it
seems that work will continue to maintain the current situation.
I hope the next owner will value the garden...

...To be honest, my wish is for it to return to the hands of the
young lady...

Taking care of the statues is tough... And I... I'm small and
petite...

La~la~.... Taking care of flowers is the happiest moment for
me....
